I think there are roughly four ways to make a stablecoin, a crypto token th=
at has a stable value of $1:
=09A dollar-backed stablecoin: You put in $1, you get a stablecoin, the iss=
uer puts the dollar somewhere safe and promises to give it back to you in e=
xchange for the stablecoin.=09An overcollateralized stablecoin: You put in =
$2 of Bitcoin or whatever, you get a $1 stablecoin, the issuer puts your Bi=
tcoin collateral=C2=A0somewhere safe and promises to give it back to you in=
 exchange for the stablecoin.=09An algorithmic stablecoin: No, bad.
  [5]

=09A stablecoin of pure will: You list a token on a crypto exchange, its na=
me is like =E2=80=9CStable Value Dollar Coin,=E2=80=9D and the marketing ma=
terials say =E2=80=9Cthe point of Stable Value Dollar Coin is to always be =
worth a dollar.=E2=80=9D And then you just hope that people will pay a doll=
ar for it, because you told them to.

I am not aware of any important examples of No. 4, but I feel like it lurks=
 in the back of the mind of a lot of crypto. A lot of crypto tokens, after =
all, have value only through collective adoption. One way to encourage that=
 adoption is to get people to think that the token=E2=80=99s value is unbou=
nded: You buy Dogecoin because you think Dogecoin will go to the moon, and =
if enough people buy it then it will. Another way to encourage that adoptio=
n, though, is to=C2=A0associate=C2=A0the token=E2=80=99s value =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0even in just a loose meme-y way =E2=80=94=C2=A0with something else valua=
ble. If you name your crypto token after Elon Musk=E2=80=99s dog, or the Gr=
eek letter omicron, then maybe it will go up when Musk=E2=80=99s dog or omi=
cron are in the news. I once proposed that a=C2=A0way to put private-compan=
y stocks on the blockchain would be to=C2=A0issue tokens with the=C2=A0name=
s=C2=A0of those private companies, and just sort of casually hope that peop=
le will buy the tokens when they think positive thoughts about the companie=
s.
Anyway someone pointed me to a Solana memecoin called =E2=80=9CCostco Hot D=
og,=E2=80=9D or COST, whose schtick is:
=09A Costco hot dog famously costs $1.50.=09This is a Costco Hot Dog. (Toke=
n.)=09Therefore this should be worth $1.50.

=E2=80=9CThe greatest meme against inflation has arrived,=E2=80=9D says its=
 X account. Sadly it=E2=80=99s trading at about $0.03 but I guess that mean=
s there=E2=80=99s a lot of upside.
  [6]


