10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Hunterbrook!</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/34902854.287353/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDEvdHJhZGUtdGhlLW5ld3MtdGhlbi1wdWJsaXNoLWl0P2NtcGlk=
PUJCRDA0MDIyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV=
0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQwMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB20b77e22" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">talked in November</a> about Hunterbrook, a=
=C2=A0hedge fund that is also a newspaper. These are mostly tough economic =
times for the news industry, and Hunterbrook hit upon a differentiated medi=
a business model:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">They would=C2=A0start a newsroom (Hun=
terbrook Media) to publish general news and investigative journalism.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There=E2=80=99s no paywall and no adve=
rtising.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But before each investiga=
tive piece is published, the newsroom would send it to Hunterbrook=E2=80=99=
s affiliated hedge fund (Hunterbrook Capital), which could trade on the new=
s.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The hedge fund=E2=80=99s tradin=
g profits can =E2=80=94=C2=A0they hope! =E2=80=94 pay the journalists=E2=80=
=99 salaries.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to think of this business model is tha=
t Hunterbrook is essentially an activist short-selling hedge fund, like Hin=
denburg Research: It investigates companies, finds problems, shorts the com=
panies, and then noisily publishes its investigation to draw attention to t=
he problems. But=C2=A0whereas Hindenburg is straightforwardly a short-selli=
ng firm, Hunterbrook=E2=80=99s news site is at least theoretically independ=
ent of its hedge fund, and if it publishes enough good general news then pe=
rhaps it can become more widely read and trusted =E2=80=94=C2=A0and have mo=
re stock-price impact =E2=80=94=C2=A0than a pure hedge fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another way to think of this business model is=
 that it is a salary arbitrage. It is expensive to hire hedge fund analysts=
 to investigate companies all over the world. It is cheaper to hire journal=
ists! You might find more tradable signals with 20 journalists than you can=
 with one hedge-fund analyst.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/34902854.287353/aHR0cHM6Ly9obnRyYnJrLmNvbS9kZWFyLXJlYWRlci8/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB86878ff3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Hunterbrook launched today</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the coming weeks and months, our investigat=
ions will expose a fossil fuel conglomerate supporting a junta, an agricult=
ural giant expanding operations in a region known for forced labor, and an =
energy company destroying an ecosystem. We believe many of the corporations=
 we will report on are also lying =E2=80=94 to customers, communities, part=
ners, shareholders, and the world.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We will be regularly publishing global news re=
ports as well, starting with foreign correspondents on the ground in Mongol=
ia, Namibia, Brazil, Vietnam, Peru, Botswana, and India. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We know this may not be seen as traditional jo=
urnalism, which is generally known for being dispassionate, reliant on insi=
de sources, and indifferent to profitability. We are proudly passionate. We=
 avoid talking to insiders, depending instead on publicly available informa=
tion.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: =
transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0And we believe that good reporting can be good business =E2=80=94=
 when you monetize insights instead of eyeballs and align profits with accu=
racy.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Smarter people have tried and failed to find a=
 sustainable model for reporting. We know this may not work. We also believ=
e it=E2=80=99s a hypothesis worth testing. Whether or not we succeed, we=E2=
=80=99re confident this team will publish meaningful reporting =E2=80=94 st=
arting today with what we believe to be the biggest mortgage scandal since =
the financial crisis.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have to say that <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34902854.287353/aHR0cHM6Ly9obnRyYnJrLmNvbS8/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5e4c1ecf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the website</a> feels more like, =
you know, Hindenburg than Bloomberg? There is a =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34902854.287353/aHR0cHM6Ly9obnRyYnJr=
LmNvbS9nbG9iYWwtbmV3cy00LTItMjAyNC8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBab71af4b" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">global news roundup</a>=E2=80=9D with economic news from the foreign co=
rrespondents, but it is kind of buried on the homepage, which is mostly dev=
oted to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34902854.2=
87353/aHR0cHM6Ly9obnRyYnJrLmNvbS91d20v/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB665852c9" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">the first big investigation</a>, about United Wholesale Mortgage, th=
e largest US mortgage lender. The gist of it is that UWM makes mortgages ex=
clusively through independent mortgage brokers, who purportedly find the be=
st deal for customers by looking at offers from lots of competing lenders, =
but many brokers send 99% of their business to UWM and can=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<=
em>really=C2=A0</em>be doing what is best for customers:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In social media posts, SEC filings, and a Supe=
r Bowl ad, UWM tells prospective homebuyers its mortgages come from brokers=
 who are =E2=80=9Cindependent.=E2=80=9D UWM has said these brokers have =E2=
=80=9Cyour best interest in mind=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cshop dozens of lende=
rs=E2=80=9D to find =E2=80=9Cthe best deal=E2=80=9D for homebuyers.=C2=A0</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But UWM deploys an arsenal of carrots and stic=
ks to =E2=80=9Ccultivate =E2=80=98loyalist=E2=80=99 brokers,=E2=80=9D as th=
e company put it in a presentation to investors. Their methods range from o=
ffering those who send UWM loans better placement in their Super Bowl-adver=
tised directory to suing brokers who shop around for better deals from cert=
ain competitors.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2021, UWM shook up the industry by changing=
 its contracts with brokers to explicitly bar them from doing business with=
 what were then two of its biggest competitors, Rocket and Fairway Independ=
ent Mortgage Corporation. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The data shows that UWM is rarely the cheapest=
 option for borrowers and certainly not the best deal anywhere close to 99%=
 of the time.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But of course I was most interested in the not=
es at the end of the report, in which Hunterbrook explains its economics. F=
or one thing, =E2=80=9CHunterbrook Capital took the following positions: Th=
e fund went short $UWMC, long $RKT, and purchased derivatives.=E2=80=9D UWM=
 Holdings Corp. fell about 7.6% just after the report was published, though=
 then it recovered most of those losses; Rocket Cos. was up a bit on the re=
port.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Short selling is not, however, the only busine=
ss model for investigative-journalism-that-is-also-a-hedge-fund, and Hunter=
brook is looking at others. There=E2=80=99s the obvious lawsuit:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hunterbrook Media and its affiliat=
es have =E2=80=A6=C2=A0submitted data analysis and research =E2=80=94 as we=
ll as the planned date of publication =E2=80=94 to Boies Schiller Flexner L=
LP, a litigation firm known for winning billions in damages from companies.=
 Hunterbrook=E2=80=99s nonprofit affiliate has entered an agreement with BS=
F in exploration of a class action lawsuit against UWM seeking restitution =
for homebuyers. If you think you are paying too much on your mortgage, visi=
t WasIRippedOff.com to learn if you might have used an independent broker w=
ho doesn=E2=80=99t shop and contact BSF.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There=E2=80=99s the only slightly less obvious=
=C2=A0=E2=80=9Ceverything is securities fraud=E2=80=9D lawsuit<a class=3D"f=
ootnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !impor=
tant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Upon publication, Hunterbrook Medi=
a plans to share this article and the data with .=E2=80=A6 shareholder liti=
gation firms whose clients own $UWMC shares and may have claims due to UWM=
=E2=80=99s governance and performance, including paying the CEO and his fam=
ily over $600 million in annual dividends despite reporting a $70 million l=
oss in 2023 by consistently missing SPAC revenue projections.=C2=A0</p></bl=
ockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And there=E2=80=99s the US Securities and Exch=
ange Commission=E2=80=99s whistleblower program:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Two of the authors of this article=
 filed a whistleblower report to the S.E.C. represented by a former S.E.C. =
Commissioner.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah. If you can find out bad news about compa=
nies, there are a lot of ways to make money. Selling ads is not one of the =
better ones!</p>
